# Quality Gates

Lint, security, build, and test failures are defects. Fix them on the branch; do not bypass hooks.

Use these gates:
- `make test`: default deterministic suite.
- `make integration`: OCR-engine, image-fixture, or external-binary tests.
- `make check-commit`: fast local gate before commit.
- `make lint`: full pre-commit run.
- `make build`: build wheel and sdist with `uv`.

Rules:
- Never use `git commit --no-verify` or skip pre-commit hooks.
- Default tests must not depend on PaddleOCR model downloads or private local files.
- Keep `extract_table_from_ocr()` covered by pure synthetic OCR examples.
- Before claiming work is complete, run the relevant fresh commands and report actual results.
